Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Remove sausage from casing if necessary; discard casing. Break up @Italian Pork Sausage Mix{9%ounce} into bite-size pieces in #oven-ready aluminum tray{}.

> For 4 servings, evenly divide sausage between two trays.

Add @Fresh Rigatoni Pasta{7%ounce}, @Peas{4%ounce}, @Romesco Sauce{6%tablespoon}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2%unit}, and 1 1/4 cups hot water. Stir to combine.

> For 4 servings, divide ingredients between two trays, using 1 1/4 cups hot water for each tray.

Cover oven-ready tray tightly with #aluminum foil{} and bake on top rack for ~{20%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, bake two trays side by side on top rack.

Carefully remove foil from tray (watch out for steam!). Gently stir pasta bake.

Return pasta bake to top rack and bake, uncovered, until pasta is al dente and sausage is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes} more. Taste and season with @Pepper{} if desired.

Divide pasta bake between shallow bowls. Top with @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon} and serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.